# Architecture Decisions

Several important long-term architectural principles were established.

## Pipeline-first Execution

Business analysis should execute through a unified pipeline rather than multiple independent workflows.

This greatly simplifies orchestration, maintenance and future extensibility.

---

## Shared Intelligence Context

Every intelligence stage should contribute to a common execution context instead of exchanging isolated results.

This enables richer reasoning across the platform.

---

## Stable Runtime

The runtime must guarantee deterministic execution regardless of pipeline complexity.

Reliability takes priority over adding new features.

---

## Backwards Compatibility

Major architectural improvements should preserve compatibility whenever possible.

Platform evolution should avoid unnecessary disruption.

